Sixty-ninth
Legislative Assembly HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 3010
of North Dakota
Introduced by
Representatives Kempenich, Berg, Christy, Fisher
Senators Hogue, Klein, Schaible
1 A concurrent resolution directing the Legislative Management to consider studying legislative
2 responsibility to carefully review and consider existing law when developing proposals to create
3 new law.
4 WHEREAS, it is a legislative responsibility to carefully review and consider existing laws
5 and regulations when developing proposals to create new laws; and
6 WHEREAS, it is a legislative responsibility to ensure a proposal to enact a new law is not
7 duplicating already existing law; and
8 WHEREAS, the careful review and consideration of existing law includes a review of
9 existing federal and state regulations and consideration of how new law would affect those
10 regulations and regulated programs;
11 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
12 NORTH DAKOTA, THE SENATE CONCURRING THEREIN:
13 That the Legislative Management consider studying legislative responsibility to carefully
14 review and consider existing law when developing proposals to create new law; and
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislative Management report its findings and
16 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
17 the Seventieth Legislative Assembly.
